cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.HC, cs.IR 

This paper focuses on using machine learning techniques to predict gender from iris images, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also evaluates the use of linear SVM and CNN, which are commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG). The use of a larger dataset and probabilistic occlusion masking suggests a focus on multimedia (cs.MM) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Finally, the paper deals with biometrics and image recognition, which could fall under information retrieval (cs.IR).
